s        Career Fairs  Gain access to over 5,000 engineering students within the UIC College of Engineering at our Fall 2020 Engineering & Computer Science Career Fair in September 2020! Come to UIC to recruit from all of our engineering and computer science majors and connect with top talent in Chicago.       career fair      SAVE THE DATE! Virtual Fall 2020 Two-Day Engineering & Computer Science Career Fair  Day 1: September 22nd |12 – 4PM | Majors: Computer Science & Computer Engineering  Day 2: September 23rd |12 – 4PM | Majors: Bioengineering, Chemical, Civil, Electrical, Industrial, & Mechanical Engineering  Employer Registration Opens Summer 2020!       Career Fair FAQ     About         About   Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, and social distancing measures in place by the state of Illinois, the Engineering Career Center will likely host a virtual career fair in Fall 2020.  We will update this website as soon as more details are confirmed. Thank you for your patience with us while we work to ensure a good recruitment experience for both employers and UIC engineering students.  The Engineering and Computer Science Career Fair is one of the largest career fairs at UIC. Previous Engineering and Computer Science Career Fairs have drawn over 100 companies and over 2,000 students to the career fair.  It is a wonderful opportunity for employers to recruit entry-level full-time engineers as well as summer interns, co-op students, or even part-time positions or contract positions.  We encourage you to review our Fall 2019 enrollment to learn more about the number of students in each engineering major at UIC.          Career Fair Schedule         Schedule   Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, and social distancing measures in place by the state of Illinois, the Engineering Career Center will likely host a virtual career fair in Fall 2020.  We will update this website as soon as more details are confirmed. Thank you for your patience with us while we work to ensure a good recruitment experience for both employers and UIC engineering students.  Schedule for BOTH FAll 2020 Career Fair Days September 22nd and September 23rd  Day 1 Majors: Computer Science & Computer Engineering  Day 2 Majors: Bioengineering, Chemical, Civil, Electrical, Industrial, & Mechanical Engineering  Detailed schedule will be announced when registration opens in Summer 2020.        Career Fair Contact Information         Contact   If you have any questions related to the Engineering and Computer Science Career Fair, please contact:   Rose Coppola-Conroy, Director   rcconroy@uic.edu  Phone: 312-355-5174             Registration Dates, Deadlines, and Payment Information         Payment   Registration Deadlines:   Deadline to Register will be announced when registration opens in Summer 2020.   Majors: All Engineering and Computer Science   Bioengineering (BioE)  Chemical Engineering (ChemE)  Civil Engineering (Civil)  Computer Science (CS)  Computer Engineering (CompE)  Electrical Engineering (EE)  Industrial Engineering (IE)  Mechanical Engineering (ME)   Career Fair Registration Single Day Rate:   TBA when registration opens in Summer 2020.   Career Fair Registration Two-Day Rate:   TBA when registration opens in Summer 2020.   Small Companies of <50 total employees: Please contact a member of the Engineering Career Center Team to discuss on-campus recruitment options.  Payment:  Credit card and check payments are accepted for the Career Fair. Please make checks payable to: University of Illinois at Chicago and send to:  University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC)  Engineering Career Center  Attn: Rose Coppola-Conroy  851 S. Morgan St., Rm 800 SEO  Chicago, IL 60607        Marketing Opportunities: Event Projectors, Weekly Email Blasts, and Poster Signage         ads   Market your company with weekly email blasts or push notifications through our career fair app.  Please note that there is limited availability for push notifications and email blasts. This website will be updated once those items are sold out.   $150: Three push notifications and a designation as a “featured” employer in our career fair app .  $350: Three weekly email blasts leading up to the career fair.   For additional questions about marketing opportunities during the career fair, please contact Rose Coppola-Conroy.  Deadline to receive a refund for Ads is Monday, September 14th.        Cancellation & Refund Policy         Refund policy   Career Fair Registration: A full refund will be provided if a cancellation is received by: Monday, September 14th at 5pm. Refunds will not be processed if an employer does not attend the fair.  Marketing Opportunities: A full refund will be provided if a cancellation is received by: Monday, September 14th at 5pm.  On Campus Interviews: Due to the high demand for on-campus interviews, cancellations will only be refunded up until Monday, September 14th at 5pm.  Inclement Weather: No refunds will be issued for cancellations caused by inclement weather, or other natural weather events that are outside of our control.        Shipping Materials to Career Fair         Shipping   For an in-person career fair, any career fair materials may be shipped to:  University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC)  Engineering Career Center  Attn: Rose Coppola-Conroy  851 S. Morgan St., Rm 800 SEO  Chicago, IL 60607  Deadline to receive all career fair materials: Friday, September 18th.  Return shipping must be arranged by the employer. At the end of the fair, please complete all shipping labels and arrange for a FedEx or UPS pickup at:  University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC)  Engineering Career Center  851 S. Morgan St., Rm 800 SEO  Chicago, IL 60607            On-Campus Interviews         OCI   On-campus interviews will be hosted virtually by UIC following the career fair throughout the month of October. We strongly recommend registering early for on-campus interviews.  Please note that due to the high demand for virtual on-campus interviews, cancellations for on-campus interviews will only be refunded until Monday, September 14th at 5pm. Any employer who cancels virtual on-campus interviews after the September 14th deadline will not be refunded.  Questions about on-campus interviews? Please contact Rose Coppola-Conroy .        Tips for Recruiters         tips   As visitors to the UIC campus, you expected to abide by University policies, including sexual harassment policies.  Before the Career Fair:   Complete all registration career fair details carefully. Information provided in your registration (company name, website, positions hiring for, etc.) will be shared with students in the career fair booklet, on the Engineering Career Center website, and our weekly e-newsletter.  We strongly encourage you to post the positions you are recruiting for in UICcareers.com . UICcareers.com is our internal job board exclusively for UIC students and recent alumni. We recommend including information about your presence at the UIC Engineering and Computer Science Career Fair in the position descriptions that you post on UICcareers.com.  If possible, we strongly encourage you to invite UIC alumni working in your companies to help staff your table during the career fair. Alumni ribbons are available at the employer check-in desks and can be a great conversation starter with UIC students.   During the Career Fair:   Please engage with students. Standing in front of your table and welcoming students to speak with you can help to create more meaningful and productive conversations.  If you are open to being contacted by students, consider bringing business cards, or cards with a general company email address on them. Students will feel much better about having a name, or at least an email, to follow-up on applications with.   After the Career Fair:   Contact students you are interested in quickly!  Consider other ways to engage with UIC students on campus via Pop-Up tables, Info Sessions, Tech Talks, On-Campus Interviews, and more. All available virtually in Fall 2020!  Contact us if you would like to learn more about additional engagement opportunities on campus, or to hear about additional upcoming career fairs hosted at UIC.                 Employers    Back to main content           Engagement Opportunities    Post Positions on UICcareers.com    2018 Employment Outcomes    Career Fairs    Professional Connections Program-Alumni Mentoring    Senior Design Expo    Hiring International Students                  UIC Logo        Engineering Career Center       Contact   851 S. Morgan St. | 800 SEO | Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-8374  rcconroy@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 